---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageSection from '../components/shell/PageSection.astro';
import Heading from '../components/ui/Heading.astro';
import Text from '../components/ui/Text.astro';
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.astro';
import GridSection from '../components/layouts/GridSection.astro';
import Badge from '../components/callouts/Badge.astro';

const navLinks = [
  { href: '#vision', label: 'Vision' },
  { href: '#components', label: 'Component Set' },
  { href: '#next', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Portfolio v2"
  description="Initial Astro scaffolding for the portfolio redesign."
  navLinks={navLinks}
>
  <main>
    <PageSection id="vision" eyebrow="Redesign In Progress" title="Portfolio v2 scaffolding">
      <Text size="lg">
        Astro is now configured to generate static assets while the Rust runtime continues to serve
        requests and WebAssembly-powered features. The shared design system will expand from these
        primitives as content migrates.
      </Text>
      <Button href="/static/index.html" variant="secondary">View legacy site</Button>
    </PageSection>

    <PageSection id="components" title="Foundational components" description="These primitives will power every page going forward.">
      <GridSection columns={3}>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <Badge tone="accent">Layout</Badge>
          <Heading level={3} size="lg">Page containers</Heading>
          <Text tone="muted">
            Container, PageSection, and flexible grid helpers keep spacing and hierarchy uniform across the experience.
          </Text>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <Badge tone="neutral">UI</Badge>
          <Heading level={3} size="lg">Buttons &amp; typography</Heading>
          <Text tone="muted">
            Token-driven Heading, Text, and Button components standardize type scale, weights, and interactive states.
          </Text>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <Badge tone="accent">Patterns</Badge>
          <Heading level={3} size="lg">Cards &amp; layouts</Heading>
          <Text tone="muted">
            Reusable cards, split sections, and callouts make it straightforward to compose project spotlights and case studies.
          </Text>
        </article>
      </GridSection>
    </PageSection>

    <PageSection id="next" title="Next steps" description="Design tokens and components are ready for page migrations.">
      <Text>
        With the component library in place, the upcoming work will focus on porting the landing page into Astro, wiring
        content collections, and iterating on accessibility. Legacy assets remain available for reference until the migration
        is complete.
      </Text>
    </PageSection>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.feature-card {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  padding: var(--space-xl);
  background: var(--color-surface-100);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  border: 1px solid rgba(17, 23, 42, 0.05);
}
</style>
